er than 100 micron) an additional source of scatter is\nprovided by AGN, where present. AGN may be detected in the near-infrared by the\nabsence of the knee, typical of stellar photospheres. However, near-infrared\ndata alone cannot constrain the level at which AGN contribute because the\ninterpretation of their observed properties, in this wave-band, depends\nstrongly on model parameters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Mar 2004 17:45:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
