ric - the unrelaxed systems are systematically 40% hotter than the\nrelaxed clusters at 2.5 sigma significance. This structural segregation should\nbe a major concern for experiments designed to constrain cosmological\nparameters using galaxy clusters. Overall our results are consistent with a\nscenario of cluster-cluster merger induced boosts to cluster X-ray luminosities\nand temperatures. [Abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Mar 2004 02:56:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
